35:19.483 --> 35:20.985
Hey, look.
I'll tell you what.

35:21.018 --> 35:23.220
Why don't I get there at 3:00 and I go
till 6:00? I'll speed as fast as I can.

35:23.253 --> 35:24.922
No. No can do.
It's a finance office.

35:24.954 --> 35:26.489
They come into work at 5:30.

35:26.523 --> 35:30.361
Well, I'm sorry, then.
I can't take it.

35:33.429 --> 35:35.698
Well, I, too, am sorry.

35:35.731 --> 35:39.536
QMB Janitorial Corporation will
no longer need your services.

35:39.570 --> 35:41.739
We'll send you your final
two paychecks by mail.

35:41.771 --> 35:43.740
Wait-- no, no--
Come on, Jerry!

35:43.773 --> 35:44.875
Look, come on, I'm never late,

35:44.907 --> 35:46.442
I work harder than
everyone else!

35:46.476 --> 35:47.612
Why are you settin' me up?

35:48.978 --> 35:50.547
Is this about the benefits?

35:50.581 --> 35:52.316
Look-- look, forget
I even asked.

35:52.349 --> 35:54.852
Look, I don't care about the benefits.
Forget it.

35:54.885 --> 35:57.788
Jerry? Jerry! Jerry!

36:09.967 --> 36:11.335
What you're doing is barbaric.

36:13.469 --> 36:15.772
I thought you stood
for something.

36:15.806 --> 36:18.576
Thank you.
I appreciate your...

36:18.608 --> 36:21.511
input. Asshole.

36:23.981 --> 36:26.317
Oh, no. Did you turn on
your phone?

36:26.349 --> 36:29.987
Uh, no. No, I'm, uh... I'm good.

36:30.019 --> 36:31.722
Uh, why don't we get outta here?

36:31.755 --> 36:33.423
Ah, yeah.

36:33.456 --> 36:36.359
I'm not like that, okay?
I'll drop you off.

36:36.393 --> 36:38.896
That's okay, I can get
my own Uber. Thank you.

36:38.929 --> 36:40.831
We can Uber together.
Let's Uber pool.

36:40.864 --> 36:43.601
It's cheap, and we may not
have jobs tomorrow, so...

36:43.634 --> 36:45.336
You know nothing about me.

36:45.369 --> 36:46.604
That's not true!

36:46.637 --> 36:47.838
I know you're from Cleveland.

36:47.871 --> 36:48.639
Oh.

36:48.672 --> 36:50.907
And I know you're an only child.

36:50.940 --> 36:53.576
And I know that you would
rather be living in New York,

36:53.610 --> 36:56.947
but Broadway is your
ex-husband's domain,

36:56.980 --> 36:59.250
so here you are,
slumming it on TV.

36:59.282 --> 37:01.951
Well, my, uh, my panties
are sopping wet.

37:01.985 --> 37:03.153
I'm not finished.

37:03.186 --> 37:05.556
I know that you eat too much
kale for your own good,

37:05.588 --> 37:08.791
and I know that you think that
real men don't drink white wine,

37:08.824 --> 37:11.294
but I don't really give
a shit because I love it.

37:15.666 --> 37:19.704
And I also know that, like me...

37:21.405 --> 37:25.776
you just want to make
something meaningful and lasting

37:25.809 --> 37:28.479
in this screwed up,

37:28.512 --> 37:32.816
swipe right, shit-for-brains
world we live in.

37:32.849 --> 37:33.884
How am I doing?

37:37.086 --> 37:40.423
You might just be the smartest
idiot that I've ever met.

37:40.456 --> 37:41.391
Really?
- Mm-hmm.

37:41.425 --> 37:42.826
Yeah, well, I did go
to Yale for two years.

37:42.858 --> 37:43.826
Did you?
- Yeah.

37:43.860 --> 37:45.829
Why did you drop out?

37:47.097 --> 37:49.700
Wouldn't you like to know?
- Mm-hmm.

37:51.400 --> 37:52.536
Let's go.

37:52.568 --> 37:53.871
This is not a yes.

37:53.903 --> 37:56.507
I never said it was a yes.

37:56.539 --> 37:57.842
O... kay.

38:10.686 --> 38:12.088
Excuse me, sir.

38:12.121 --> 38:15.826
Uh, the dishwasher
you've got, the old guy?

38:15.858 --> 38:16.994
He's a real dick.

38:18.561 --> 38:20.630
Him.

38:20.664 --> 38:23.334
<i>A new show aired
on the WBC network last night.</i>

38:23.367 --> 38:27.403
The incredible thing is the show
seemingly came out of nowhere.

38:27.436 --> 38:30.007
No press, no advertising, nada.

38:30.039 --> 38:32.675
<i>Now, if it turns out to be real,</i>

38:32.708 --> 38:35.978
<i>WBC is gonna have a lot
to answer for.</i>

38:36.012 --> 38:37.881
Just take a look
at our Facebook page.

38:37.914 --> 38:40.384
People are enraged.

38:40.416 --> 38:43.653
<i>I'm taking callers.
First up, Ne--</i>

38:46.856 --> 38:49.625
Holy shit.

38:51.628 --> 38:53.530
Okay, okay!

38:53.563 --> 38:56.400
Hey, hey, hey!

38:56.432 --> 38:57.434
Karina, what the f-

38:57.467 --> 38:59.435
Now I know why you've
been hiding from me.

38:59.469 --> 39:00.804
Uh, can we talk about
this later, please?

39:00.836 --> 39:02.739
You told me that you
were getting out.

39:02.773 --> 39:04.675
I did get out. This is
not a reality show.

39:04.708 --> 39:05.843
No shit, it's worse.

39:05.876 --> 39:07.644
Can we-- can we-- seriously.
- No, no, no, no.

39:07.677 --> 39:09.445
Everybody at work knows
that I'm your sister.

39:09.478 --> 39:12.715
I don't-- you-- you can't
fucking do this to me!

39:12.748 --> 39:14.884
What? I'm not-- this is not about you.
- Are you kidding me?

39:14.918 --> 39:16.086
Adam, have you got my phone?

39:16.119 --> 39:18.789
Oh, I'm... sorry.

39:18.822 --> 39:22.826
Hey. Uh, uh, Sylvia, this is
my sister, Karina.

39:22.858 --> 39:24.460
Karina, Sylvia.

39:24.494 --> 39:25.496
Hi.

39:26.530 --> 39:28.732
Hi. Girlfriend?

39:28.764 --> 39:29.732
Yeah.
- No.

39:29.766 --> 39:32.970
No, no.
I am his producer

39:33.003 --> 39:37.408
and this was a drunken decision.

39:37.440 --> 39:39.643
Come on.
Transparency, right?

39:39.675 --> 39:41.177
Sylvia, I don't like your show.

39:41.210 --> 39:42.645
Oh, neither do I.

39:42.679 --> 39:43.914
Trust me.

39:45.548 --> 39:47.751
Okay.

39:47.784 --> 39:50.153
I like her, Adam.
Don't fuck it up.

39:50.186 --> 39:51.788
Thanks for your input.

39:54.623 --> 39:55.625
Shut up.

39:55.659 --> 39:57.494
<i>Our country has never been</i>

39:57.527 --> 39:59.195
<i>more politically
or socially fractured.</i>

39:59.228 --> 40:02.465
<i>People watch and read
the news they agree with.</i>

40:02.498 --> 40:05.501
<i>There's no dissenting
opinion anymore.</i>

40:05.534 --> 40:08.538
<i>There's no honest debate.
It's just theatrics.</i>

40:08.572 --> 40:09.974
<i>This whole show is theatrics.</i>

40:10.007 --> 40:12.842
<i>Wait a second. Are you
talking about our show or theirs?</i>

40:12.876 --> 40:15.446
Hi, daddy.
How was work?

40:15.478 --> 40:17.747
It was fantastic.
How was your sleep?

40:17.780 --> 40:20.049
They cut our cable
and internet last night.

40:20.083 --> 40:21.218
I see.

40:21.251 --> 40:24.488
Well, more time to read, hit
the books and study, right?

40:24.521 --> 40:25.489
Dad, is everything o--

40:25.521 --> 40:27.824
Hey, you got any tests today?

40:30.827 --> 40:32.563
History.
- Are you ready?

40:32.596 --> 40:33.630
Of course, but can we--

40:33.664 --> 40:35.899
Who was the 16th president
of the United States?

40:35.931 --> 40:37.000
Abe Lincoln, but--

40:37.032 --> 40:38.534
And who was the 17th?

40:38.568 --> 40:41.071
I don't know. My test
is on the Civil War.

40:41.103 --> 40:42.304
So what?

40:42.338 --> 40:45.107
The future president's gotta know
all his predecessors, right?

40:45.141 --> 40:48.711
I guess so.

40:51.081 --> 40:54.617
<i>...salacious,
and downright unconscionable.</i>

40:54.650 --> 40:56.219
<i>Not only should it be taken
off the air,</i>

40:56.253 --> 40:57.888
<i>the creator should be jailed!</i>

40:57.920 --> 40:59.088
<i>Oh, come on now.</i>

40:59.121 --> 41:01.692
<i>It's provocative, yes,</i>

41:01.724 --> 41:05.027
<i>but what if we take Adam Rogers
seriously for a moment?</i>

41:05.061 --> 41:06.028
<i>What if he's right?</i>

41:06.061 --> 41:09.599
<i>What if this show is exactly
what we need--</i>

41:09.632 --> 41:11.134
All right, little man.

41:11.166 --> 41:12.668
I'm gonna prep you for surgery.

41:12.702 --> 41:15.038
Last check-up before I go.

41:15.070 --> 41:17.507
How are you feeling?
You still nauseous?

41:17.541 --> 41:19.776
I'm fine, but the news
has been crapping

41:19.809 --> 41:22.546
all over your brother
this morning.

41:22.579 --> 41:24.715
I don't want you watching that garbage.
You're too young.

41:24.748 --> 41:27.684
Please.
I'm as mature as you.

41:27.717 --> 41:28.719
Funny man, huh?

41:32.322 --> 41:35.259
You're not gonna worry, right?
Routine procedure.

41:35.291 --> 41:37.860
That's what they always say.

41:37.893 --> 41:40.696
You're gonna be just fine.
- That too.

41:40.730 --> 41:44.934
But my favorite one
is "you're so strong".

41:49.606 --> 41:51.975
It's the water commission.

41:52.007 --> 41:53.943
They call at 9:00,
right after the cable company,

41:53.976 --> 41:56.980
who won't be calling no more
'cause it's shut down.

41:57.012 --> 41:59.083
I lost my job.

42:00.951 --> 42:01.985
Which one?

42:03.586 --> 42:04.588
Both of them.

42:07.356 --> 42:09.293
Dare I ask why?

42:09.326 --> 42:10.661
Does it matter?

42:13.896 --> 42:17.134
Okay. Okay, I can
pick up the slack.

42:18.601 --> 42:20.170
I'll try to get some
more hours at the hotel

42:20.202 --> 42:21.838
and I'll join Mary Kay.

42:21.871 --> 42:23.240
I can sew--
- Rebecca.

42:23.273 --> 42:25.842
I can sell Tupperware,
I can sell vitamins--

42:25.875 --> 42:28.110
Rebecca, I'm not giving up.
- I know.

42:28.143 --> 42:30.947
But I don't think you
understand what I'm saying.

42:34.117 --> 42:37.754
You lose this house
and you lose us.

42:43.226 --> 42:46.663
Hello, this is Mason Washington.
The money's coming.

42:46.695 --> 42:48.764
I appreciate your patience.
Thank you.

42:50.132 --> 42:53.636
We quintupled our audience twice
over from beginning to end,

42:53.670 --> 42:55.938
and that's not even counting
plus three and plus five.

42:55.972 --> 42:58.075
Does this mean that we're number--
- Number three.

42:58.108 --> 43:00.911
Behind NBC and CBS, but still.

43:00.943 --> 43:03.313
With no press, no promotion?
Not bad.

43:03.346 --> 43:04.947
We're gonna be
number one next week.

43:04.981 --> 43:06.683
That's a ten million
viewer jump.

43:06.715 --> 43:08.652
Yeah, I understand
ratings share.

43:09.753 --> 43:11.788
Holy shit.
- All right, hot shot.

43:11.820 --> 43:12.956
Here's my concern.

43:14.157 --> 43:17.627
People are going to tire of
giving contestants pity money.

43:17.661 --> 43:19.028
Okay, first of all,
they're not contestants,

43:19.061 --> 43:20.896
and it's not pity money.
- Oh, you know what I mean.

43:20.929 --> 43:23.666
We are giving our audience
the power to enact change,

43:23.699 --> 43:26.068
to empathize with the
people they relate to.

43:26.101 --> 43:27.403
It's not gonna get
too old, too fast.

43:27.436 --> 43:29.172
Oh, yeah, it will.
Trust me.

43:29.204 --> 43:32.241
You created an event.
We need a show.

43:32.275 --> 43:34.177
We'll just bring
more people on each week.

43:34.210 --> 43:35.746
We'll pick up the pace.
- Done.

43:35.778 --> 43:38.047
But that doesn't address
my main concern.

43:38.081 --> 43:39.048
Which is what?

43:39.081 --> 43:41.719
You need this audience
as much as I do, Adam.

43:44.387 --> 43:45.956
I'll keep them invested.

44:01.905 --> 44:07.044
Last week an American
ended her life

44:07.077 --> 44:09.913
right in front of you
on national television.

44:09.945 --> 44:12.081
It was shocking.

44:12.114 --> 44:16.085
Some say it was appalling...

44:16.119 --> 44:17.387
but it was real.

44:21.123 --> 44:24.927
We changed a young girl's
life for the better.

44:24.960 --> 44:26.962
Now, if you don't like
what we're doing here,

44:26.996 --> 44:29.298
please, change the channel.

44:29.331 --> 44:32.234
Close your browser,
file a complaint,

44:32.268 --> 44:34.271
or simply turn it off.

44:34.304 --> 44:36.873
Will this fellow ever
follow the script?

44:36.905 --> 44:40.844
But I'm willing to bet
that you won't.

44:40.876 --> 44:43.012
Because, deep down, you know

44:43.045 --> 44:45.748
that what we're doing here
is important.

44:47.182 --> 44:48.951
You're angry.

44:48.985 --> 44:51.887
You want change.

44:51.920 --> 44:56.259
You believe in the value
of life.

44:56.291 --> 44:58.394
Well, guess what?
So do I.

44:58.427 --> 45:00.130
And so do our three guests
tonight.

45:00.163 --> 45:01.197
Cue applause.

45:07.936 --> 45:10.139
It seems my producers want
me to get on with the show.

45:10.172 --> 45:11.808
Cue applause.

45:24.387 --> 45:27.457
Friends...

45:27.489 --> 45:31.861
last week you also changed
a young girl's life.

45:31.894 --> 45:37.067
$300,000 was raised
for Emily Hickey.

45:37.099 --> 45:40.269
$300,000!

45:40.302 --> 45:43.873
Over 100 of you even called in
offering to be her foster parent.

45:45.909 --> 45:52.750
And because of you, and you,
and you, and you...

45:54.951 --> 45:56.920
Emily will find a safe home.

45:58.021 --> 46:01.525
She'll go to college, she'll get
a degree

46:01.557 --> 46:03.994
and fulfill her mother's dreams.

46:12.302 --> 46:15.905
You have all lead by example,

46:15.938 --> 46:19.275
and the WBC network
heard you loud and clear.

46:19.309 --> 46:23.547
So from here on in...

46:23.579 --> 46:26.949
we will be donating $250,000

46:26.983 --> 46:29.586
to the guest that you believe
deserves it the most.

46:29.619 --> 46:32.255
All you have to do is vote.

46:35.123 --> 46:36.326
We go from one death to three,

46:36.358 --> 46:37.927
and now we're doing
death of the week?

46:37.960 --> 46:39.929
Was this your idea?

46:39.963 --> 46:41.265
He's flying solo, but I like it.

46:41.297 --> 46:44.466
I just have to convince our board
of directors to play along.

46:44.500 --> 46:46.436
He's gonna get himself fired.

46:46.469 --> 46:49.873
Yeah, or make himself
indispensable.

46:49.905 --> 46:51.507
All right, put me in his ear.

46:53.976 --> 46:56.612
Adam, you crazy son of a bitch.

46:56.646 --> 46:58.849
<i>We're a go.</i>

47:06.989 --> 47:10.292
<i>Please welcome Adam Rogers!</i>

47:10.326 --> 47:11.894
Let's get started.

47:11.927 --> 47:14.431
Introducing Timothy Reyes.

47:14.463 --> 47:17.099
Timothy was diagnosed with ALS

47:17.132 --> 47:20.369
and has come to share
his last moments with us.

47:39.322 --> 47:41.490
Please welcome Ellen Black.

47:41.523 --> 47:43.460
Ellen wants to donate
her potential winnings

47:43.492 --> 47:45.895
to aid Syrian refugees.

48:07.617 --> 48:10.487
<i>This is David Williams.</i>

48:10.519 --> 48:13.657
David's wife needs
a heart transplant.

48:13.690 --> 48:17.461
With no donors in sight,
he's giving his own.

48:24.400 --> 48:25.367
Do it already!

48:25.400 --> 48:27.503
Ah!

48:39.282 --> 48:40.583
Don't you think it's horrible?

48:40.615 --> 48:42.652
I do.
- So why do you do it?

48:42.684 --> 48:44.586
Because I saw somebody die,

48:44.619 --> 48:47.156
murdered, right in front
of me, not too long ago.

48:47.190 --> 48:50.025
It was a senseless
waste of life,

48:50.059 --> 48:51.995
but the deaths
on my show are not.

48:52.027 --> 48:55.397
The number one show in
the United States of America.

48:56.798 --> 48:59.101
<i>But you're profiting
off of other people's misery.</i>

48:59.135 --> 49:02.539
Isn't everybody profiting off
of other people's misery, Mark?

49:02.572 --> 49:04.307
The churches profit,
the banks profit,

49:04.340 --> 49:06.276
the fast food companies profit.

49:06.309 --> 49:07.711
Journalists
just like you profit.

49:07.744 --> 49:10.512
Don't think that you're above
this, because you're not.

49:10.545 --> 49:13.415
Besides, I'm not doing
this for the money.

49:13.449 --> 49:14.717
What are you doing it for then?

49:14.751 --> 49:17.420
I'm doing it because television
needs a wake-up call, that's why.

49:17.452 --> 49:18.688
<i>We're in pain.
We're alone.</i>

49:21.623 --> 49:22.759
<i>We need to connect again.</i>

49:22.791 --> 49:25.996
<i>We need to bridge the social,
racial and political divide,</i>

49:26.028 --> 49:28.664
<i>and I think--
Actually, I believe</i>

49:28.697 --> 49:30.699
that we are the catalyst for
that change.

49:32.367 --> 49:34.538
Adam Rogers for president!

49:55.791 --> 49:58.560
I can almost guarantee you
number one all across the world.

49:58.594 --> 49:59.862
What do you guys say?

49:59.896 --> 50:02.532
Oh, I love to hear it. I love to hear it.
Thank you so much.

50:04.500 --> 50:05.501
Try one with a smile.

50:09.172 --> 50:11.074
<i>When will it be enough?</i>

50:11.106 --> 50:13.143
That's a good question.
I don't know.

50:13.175 --> 50:14.677
When people stop watching,
I guess.

50:14.710 --> 50:17.679
When they don't need us anymore.

50:17.713 --> 50:19.816
But right now they do.

50:38.835 --> 50:42.105
Oh!

50:42.137 --> 50:46.175
<i>This Is Your Death!
This Is Your Death!</i>

50:46.208 --> 50:48.744
<i>This Is Your Death!</i>

50:48.777 --> 50:51.747
<i>This Is Your Death!</i>

50:51.780 --> 50:54.349
<i>This Is Your Death!</i>

50:58.887 --> 51:00.222
Sylvia.

51:02.425 --> 51:03.793
I owe you a drink.

51:05.894 --> 51:08.164
Look, we're a team
and I feel like...

51:09.632 --> 51:12.268
I-I guess I feel like I could
be keeping you in the loop

51:12.300 --> 51:14.436
more than I have been.

51:14.469 --> 51:16.138
And a drink is gonna solve that?

51:16.172 --> 51:17.773
No, but four might.

51:19.375 --> 51:20.510
All right.
Good night.

51:20.543 --> 51:22.811
Hey.
You can hate me,

51:22.844 --> 51:24.179
you can hate
what we're doing here,

51:24.213 --> 51:25.849
but you can't deny
that we're a good team.

51:25.882 --> 51:27.617
We're not a team.
- Yes, we are!

51:27.650 --> 51:29.485
No! No, come on.

51:29.518 --> 51:32.187
You just do whatever you want
and I clean up your messes.

51:32.221 --> 51:33.322
Right.

51:33.356 --> 51:36.392
One of these days
I will stop, though.

51:36.425 --> 51:38.528
We have the number one show
on television.

51:38.561 --> 51:40.797
I made you rich.

51:40.829 --> 51:42.699
I mean, what else do you want?

51:44.400 --> 51:45.501
<i>What else do you want?</i>

51:45.534 --> 51:47.536
I want a drink.

51:47.570 --> 51:49.239
Maybe a sleepover.

51:50.907 --> 51:52.209
Good night, Adam.

51:57.313 --> 51:59.148
I'll take you up on that drink.

52:04.387 --> 52:06.789
You Washington?
- Yeah.

52:06.822 --> 52:08.590
You the foreman?
- Yep.

52:08.623 --> 52:12.261
It's nice to see you.
I've got you my résumé.

52:14.429 --> 52:16.365
Oh, uh, you think about dyin'?

52:16.398 --> 52:18.400
Excuse me?

52:18.434 --> 52:19.869
Oh yeah, that.

52:19.902 --> 52:21.737
Yeah, that's the truth.

52:21.771 --> 52:22.906
You gotta see it.

52:24.606 --> 52:27.943
Anyhow, this is a union job.

52:27.976 --> 52:30.712
How do you have so much
experience with no union card?

52:30.746 --> 52:34.951
Oh, well, I was, uh... a
temp filler over in Chicago,

52:34.983 --> 52:37.519
and it kinda, you know, basically
turned into a full-time job.

52:37.552 --> 52:38.654
Fuckin' Chicago.

52:38.688 --> 52:41.291
Yeah, well, you got that right.

52:41.324 --> 52:46.896
Well, we're looking to fill
the 8:00 to 6:00 spot.

52:46.929 --> 52:48.831
That's pm to am.

52:48.864 --> 52:50.666
You'll need to join the
longshoremen's union, too,

52:50.699 --> 52:52.768
so there'll be some upfront
costs there, as well.

52:52.802 --> 52:54.871
Hey, no problem.
I get benefits, right?

52:54.903 --> 52:57.940
Oh, yeah, yeah.

52:57.974 --> 52:59.843
It happens
all the time. Look.

53:01.577 --> 53:03.780
Now I'm gonna need to see

53:03.813 --> 53:06.383
your forklift certification
for ocean.

53:10.418 --> 53:11.554
Is there a problem?

53:12.554 --> 53:14.456
Listen, I need this job bad.

53:14.489 --> 53:15.991
Now, I can do anything
your guys can do,

53:16.025 --> 53:18.728
I just don't have any forklift
experience, but I'm a quick study.

53:18.760 --> 53:21.431
Trust me.
- Can you lash a ship?

53:21.463 --> 53:23.299
Of course.
- What's lashing, then?

53:24.500 --> 53:27.971
I'm sorry, Mr. Washington.

53:28.003 --> 53:29.438
We don't have the time
or resources

53:29.472 --> 53:31.007
to be training greenhorns
right now,

53:31.039 --> 53:32.442
especially someone
as old as you.

53:32.474 --> 53:33.576
Please, sir.
Look, I got a family,

53:33.610 --> 53:35.878
I got two kids, I got a
house I'm about to lose.

53:35.911 --> 53:37.646
I'll do anything you ask.

53:37.679 --> 53:40.916
Brunt labor, overtime,
janitorial.

53:40.949 --> 53:43.685
You wanna go clean toilets?
Go talk to the port.

53:43.719 --> 53:45.588
Wait, no, no, wait, wait,
wait! Hold on, man.

53:45.621 --> 53:47.356
Don't-- don't turn
your back on me.

53:47.389 --> 53:48.590
Look, I'm out of options!

53:48.623 --> 53:50.025
Get out of my way, son!

53:51.427 --> 53:52.961
You usually call
your elders "son"?

53:55.597 --> 53:57.266
Go fuck yourself!

53:59.869 --> 54:01.238
Aaargh!

54:02.672 --> 54:04.840
Time to call the janitor, boss!

54:17.385 --> 54:19.422
Jesus.
- Move forward. Right there.

54:19.454 --> 54:20.690
Ah...

54:26.429 --> 54:29.532
Holy shit.
- Yeah. Yeah, right?

54:29.565 --> 54:30.900
Look at this.
My favorite part.

54:30.932 --> 54:32.302
Come here, come here, come here.

54:34.536 --> 54:36.438
See that casita back there?

54:36.472 --> 54:39.709
Two bedrooms, full kitchen,
and it's got your name on it.

54:39.742 --> 54:42.345
I can't afford that.

54:42.378 --> 54:44.447
You really think I'm
gonna make you pay rent?

54:44.480 --> 54:47.317
You can stay there for free
as long as you want.

54:47.349 --> 54:50.353
Okay? All you gotta do is, you
know, save up for your own place.

54:50.385 --> 54:52.788
Adam, I got six-figure
credit card debt to pay off

54:52.822 --> 54:54.356
before I can even think
about buying a house.

54:54.389 --> 54:55.391
Right, right, right.

54:55.423 --> 54:58.894
Right?
- That reminds me.

54:59.994 --> 55:01.431
Come on.

55:06.501 --> 55:09.971
I'm not making you rich, I'm
just putting you back to zero.

55:10.005 --> 55:12.474
No. Adam, I can't.

55:12.507 --> 55:14.009
I-I haven't seen you
in three months,

55:14.043 --> 55:15.778
you know you're my only friend.

55:15.811 --> 55:17.880
I-I know, I know.
And I'm sorry.

55:17.913 --> 55:20.083
I've just been...
I've been really busy.

55:21.751 --> 55:24.019
Would you look at yourself?

55:24.052 --> 55:25.621
Would you look at this house?

55:25.653 --> 55:28.623
This is sick.
- Yeah.

55:28.657 --> 55:30.727
Yeah, you mean sick like cool?

55:30.760 --> 55:31.994
Because...
- No.

55:32.027 --> 55:34.364
Because I agree.
- No, Adam, I'm not joking,

55:34.396 --> 55:35.864
and I do not want
your blood money.

55:37.065 --> 55:41.002
You're my sister and I love you,
and you've been doing so well

55:41.036 --> 55:42.838
and I promised that I was
gonna take care of you.

55:42.871 --> 55:45.674
At what cost, Adam?
- What do you mean, at what cost?

55:45.708 --> 55:49.144
How many people had to
die for this house?

55:49.177 --> 55:51.646
For that check?

55:51.679 --> 55:54.916
Ten? 30? 50?

55:54.949 --> 55:56.718
Oh, Jesus Christ.
Don't be ridiculous.

55:56.751 --> 55:57.987
Is death ridiculous to you now?

55:58.019 --> 55:59.121
No, it isn't--
- Do you know what I do?

55:59.155 --> 56:02.024
No, it's not ridiculous,
and if you watched my show,

56:02.056 --> 56:04.593
you'd know that I take
my job very seriously.

56:04.626 --> 56:06.695
By showing death,
I am single-handedly

56:06.728 --> 56:08.130
changing people's
approach to life.

56:08.164 --> 56:09.565
The world's finally waking up.

56:09.597 --> 56:11.634
You are a fucking game
show host, Adam!

56:11.666 --> 56:14.503
And that is all!

56:14.536 --> 56:16.505
Wake up!

56:29.885 --> 56:32.822
<i>And now, your host, Adam Rogers!</i>

56:36.625 --> 56:37.827
Thank you.

56:43.798 --> 56:49.538
So I had an interesting and sobering
conversation with my sister today,

56:49.572 --> 56:51.641
and in the name of transparency,

56:51.673 --> 56:53.175
I thought I would
share it with you.

56:53.208 --> 56:54.309
Oh, no.

56:54.344 --> 56:59.715
She thinks that what we're
doing here is abominable.

57:02.217 --> 57:04.519
No, no, no. It's okay.
It's okay.

57:04.552 --> 57:07.589
Camera one.
- Dissenting opinion is okay.

57:07.623 --> 57:08.858
Camera three.

57:08.891 --> 57:11.693
But what really got me was when
she called it a game show,

57:11.726 --> 57:12.994
as if--

57:13.028 --> 57:16.766
Yeah, yeah, as if all that was
at stake here is the money.

57:16.798 --> 57:19.001
Cut to one.

57:19.034 --> 57:21.103
Yeah, I know.
It hurt me, too.

57:21.135 --> 57:23.873
<i>It was ignorant.</i>

57:23.905 --> 57:25.574
<i>And insensitive.</i>

57:27.775 --> 57:28.976
<i>Not to me, but to the folks</i>

57:29.010 --> 57:33.148
<i>who have literally given
their lives for a higher cause.</i>

57:33.181 --> 57:35.517
<i>And the fact that it came
from my own sister,</i>

57:35.550 --> 57:39.221
<i>the only family member
that I have left in this world.</i>

57:41.023 --> 57:42.892
<i>I guess that just made it hurt
even worse.</i>

57:47.295 --> 57:48.931
We'll be back
after these messages

57:48.963 --> 57:50.866
<i>with more This Is Your Death.</i>

57:58.673 --> 58:00.509
<i>- What?
- Hi, Karina?</i>

58:00.543 --> 58:02.612
It's Sylvia. He really doesn't
mean what he's saying.

58:02.644 --> 58:03.612
How did you get my number?

58:03.646 --> 58:04.914
<i>You're Adam's emergency contact.</i>

58:04.947 --> 58:07.148
<i>- Fuck him.
- I'm sorry I'm calling you, but I--</i>

58:07.181 --> 58:09.050
Fuck you.
- I agree.

58:09.083 --> 58:11.152
Fuck both of us. Just please,
please don't blame yourself.

58:11.186 --> 58:15.557
<i>Uh, Adam told me a little bit
about your history and...</i>

58:15.590 --> 58:19.728
<i>I really don't mean to pry but I think
it might be a good idea to call someone.</i>

58:19.762 --> 58:21.230
I don't need a fucking
therapist right now.

58:21.262 --> 58:23.098
I need to relax.

58:23.132 --> 58:27.202
What happened to my brother?!!

58:27.235 --> 58:29.771
I don't know.

58:29.804 --> 58:32.541
I really don't know.

58:32.574 --> 58:33.708
I'm so sorry.

58:43.619 --> 58:44.987
On in 25.

58:45.019 --> 58:47.989
Listen, I-- I have
to keep running this show,

58:48.023 --> 58:49.925
but I'm not getting
off the phone

58:49.958 --> 58:51.960
until you tell me
you're gonna be okay.

59:01.269 --> 59:03.739
Okay, I'll call.

59:04.773 --> 59:06.209
I owe you one.

59:08.911 --> 59:10.046
Stay on.

59:12.947 --> 59:14.817
In time.

59:14.849 --> 59:18.820
On in five, four, three...

59:22.724 --> 59:24.326
Standby VTR.

59:24.360 --> 59:26.762
Ladies and gentlemen,
what are we here to do?

59:26.795 --> 59:29.298
To change.

59:29.331 --> 59:31.834
And what are we gonna change?
- The world!

59:31.867 --> 59:34.202
<i>- I'm sorry, what are we gonna change?
- Adam's on here next.</i>

59:34.235 --> 59:36.004
<i>- The world!
- What're you guys watching?</i>

59:36.038 --> 59:39.641
Derrick made an antenna.
We got basic cable back.

59:39.675 --> 59:42.178
<i>- What're we here to do?
- Don't watch this trash.</i>

59:42.210 --> 59:44.947
It ain't trash, pops.
It's people like us.

59:47.715 --> 59:49.317
Dad!
- Mason!

59:49.351 --> 59:52.121
Those people are not like us.

59:52.153 --> 59:53.556
They're poor and desperate.

59:53.588 --> 59:56.891
They're sacrificing themselves for
the betterment of their families.

59:56.925 --> 59:59.061
Do these four walls look
poor and desperate to you?

59:59.094 --> 01:00:00.262
Mason.
- No!

01:00:00.295 --> 01:00:02.999
Do you know how hard I worked
to get you into a good school

01:00:03.032 --> 01:00:04.834
so you could do things I
could never dream of doing?

01:00:04.867 --> 01:00:06.869
Yeah, dad, I do.

01:00:06.902 --> 01:00:10.039
And I also know that we're
about to lose it all.

01:00:10.072 --> 01:00:12.008
What? You think
I'm dumb?

01:00:12.041 --> 01:00:15.978
You think I don't hear you
and mom arguing every night?

01:00:16.010 --> 01:00:18.648
I tried talking to you
like a million times,

01:00:18.681 --> 01:00:22.050
and every time you shut
me down like I'm a kid.

01:00:22.083 --> 01:00:24.886
But I'm not.

01:00:24.920 --> 01:00:28.257
My crutches are six
inches too small,

01:00:28.289 --> 01:00:30.659
but I don't say nothing,

01:00:30.693 --> 01:00:33.663
'cause I know that you
can't afford to fix it.

01:00:33.695 --> 01:00:35.797
So you want to deal
with this by yourself?

01:00:35.831 --> 01:00:38.668
Then fucking deal with it, okay?

01:00:53.382 --> 01:00:55.818
Ladies and gentlemen, please
welcome our next guest.

01:00:55.851 --> 01:00:58.688
This is Meg Waters,
here to remind us

01:00:58.721 --> 01:01:03.358
that not all soldiers are ordered
to fight the good fight.

01:01:18.840 --> 01:01:21.143
Not all soldiers are ordered
to fight the good fight, huh?

01:01:21.175 --> 01:01:22.277
That includes us.

01:01:22.311 --> 01:01:23.979
Yeah, no, I understand metaphor.

01:01:24.012 --> 01:01:25.247
You fucking prick.
- I'm sorry,

01:01:25.280 --> 01:01:27.283
was that a metaphor or a simile?

01:01:27.315 --> 01:01:31.019
It's a statement.
Hey, call your sister.

01:01:31.052 --> 01:01:33.088
She saw what you said and
she's having a breakdown.

01:01:33.121 --> 01:01:34.824
Well, that's not the first time.

01:01:34.856 --> 01:01:36.092
I'll call her after the show.

01:01:36.125 --> 01:01:39.461
Adam--
- After the show, Sylvia.

01:01:39.494 --> 01:01:42.130
She's why you quit Yale,
isn't she?

01:01:48.170 --> 01:01:50.972
We're losing the audience.
They can't see.

01:01:51.005 --> 01:01:52.774
This is a bad idea.

01:01:52.807 --> 01:01:54.409
Cue the heartbeats.

01:02:04.887 --> 01:02:07.823
I-I-- Is she passed out?

01:02:07.856 --> 01:02:09.759
Can I get the interior car view?

01:02:09.791 --> 01:02:10.925
Cue camera one.

01:02:10.958 --> 01:02:13.495
Stand by, car cam 2.

01:02:15.530 --> 01:02:17.333
Guys, I can't see shit.

01:02:17.365 --> 01:02:19.534
<i>- Is she dead?
- Her heart monitor says no,</i>

01:02:19.568 --> 01:02:21.203
but it shouldn't be more
than two minutes.

01:02:21.235 --> 01:02:22.871
Put up the facts about the CO2.

01:02:22.905 --> 01:02:24.507
<i>- Insert CO2 details.
- She's not dying!</i>

01:02:27.108 --> 01:02:28.277
She's not dying!

01:02:28.309 --> 01:02:30.112
We're losing our audience.

01:02:30.144 --> 01:02:32.815
Come on, get
your shit together out there.

01:02:32.847 --> 01:02:34.983
This is fucking boring.
Kill it.

01:02:35.016 --> 01:02:37.285
We can't fake a death!
Adam, back me up here.

01:02:37.318 --> 01:02:39.154
<i>We are all about
transparency, am I right?</i>

01:02:39.188 --> 01:02:41.490
<i>We're not faking a death.</i>

01:02:41.523 --> 01:02:43.760
She can die backstage
for all I care.

01:02:50.298 --> 01:02:51.601
Let her finish backstage.

01:02:51.634 --> 01:02:54.269
<i>- Adam, I really don't think that's--
- Just do it.</i>

01:02:59.173 --> 01:03:01.143
Okay, slow down the heartbeat.

01:03:01.175 --> 01:03:03.045
Slower.

01:03:03.077 --> 01:03:05.181
Slower.

01:03:05.213 --> 01:03:07.449
And kill it.

01:03:18.059 --> 01:03:21.864
Ladies and gentlemen, Meg Waters.

01:03:21.896 --> 01:03:23.498
Come on, people, Meg Waters.

01:03:26.001 --> 01:03:27.269
There we go.

01:03:31.572 --> 01:03:35.243
<i>We'll be back with more This
Is Your Death right after this.</i>

01:03:38.480 --> 01:03:40.248
Whoa, did you see that?

01:03:41.884 --> 01:03:43.552
She's not dead!
Did anyone see that?

01:03:44.952 --> 01:03:45.987
Damn.

01:03:48.190 --> 01:03:49.192
Fuck.

01:03:52.628 --> 01:03:53.996
Excuse me.

01:04:03.572 --> 01:04:05.575
Hello!
Thank you. Yeah.

01:04:11.346 --> 01:04:12.882
She isn't out yet.
Can I get her out?

01:04:12.914 --> 01:04:14.983
No, no, no. Don't touch
it, don't touch it.

01:04:15.016 --> 01:04:17.485
If we pull her out and
she dies, it's on us.

01:04:21.222 --> 01:04:23.226
Give me that. Okay.
- Yeah.

01:04:32.034 --> 01:04:33.469
Shit.

01:04:35.536 --> 01:04:38.172
Okay. Okay, everything's
gonna be okay.

01:04:38.206 --> 01:04:40.009
Jesus Christ!

01:04:43.411 --> 01:04:44.980
No, no, no. No!
- Let me out, please!

01:04:58.492 --> 01:05:00.630
The world is a better place
because of our show.

01:05:02.297 --> 01:05:05.134
To heal, we need to see pain,

01:05:05.166 --> 01:05:06.969
and our cause is too important

01:05:07.001 --> 01:05:10.172
to be hijacked by a woman
who had second thoughts!

01:05:10.204 --> 01:05:12.208
She chose this!

01:05:14.342 --> 01:05:17.045
She chose this. Hey.

01:05:22.516 --> 01:05:25.587
Jesus Christ.
Die already.

01:05:27.289 --> 01:05:30.726
Okay. Just let me
handle this.

01:05:30.759 --> 01:05:32.661
Just let me handle this.

01:05:32.693 --> 01:05:35.331
Good work.
Good work.

01:05:50.679 --> 01:05:52.181
It's okay!

01:06:32.253 --> 01:06:33.521
Take care of it.

01:06:37.059 --> 01:06:40.162
All right, people,
we're back in 15 seconds.

01:07:01.449 --> 01:07:03.351
They think we faked her death.

01:07:04.652 --> 01:07:07.255
What happened in the car, Adam?

01:07:08.489 --> 01:07:12.160
Ilana told me our
numbers are down.

01:07:12.193 --> 01:07:14.563
I think people
are getting bored.

01:07:14.596 --> 01:07:15.764
We need to up the stakes.

01:07:15.797 --> 01:07:17.800
What happened in the car, Adam?

01:07:19.201 --> 01:07:21.570
Nothing.

01:07:21.603 --> 01:07:24.240
Turns out she died
on stage, after all.

01:07:29.610 --> 01:07:33.347
No more staging
anti-climactic deaths.

01:07:33.380 --> 01:07:35.716
We need "boom."

01:07:35.750 --> 01:07:37.652
What about their
reasons for dying?

01:07:37.686 --> 01:07:41.423
Isn't that the most
important thing?

01:07:41.456 --> 01:07:43.059
Hmm?

01:07:45.226 --> 01:07:47.528
Nothing.

01:07:47.561 --> 01:07:49.730
Ilana.
- All right. Get going.

01:07:49.764 --> 01:07:52.634
Excuse me.
I have an idea.

01:07:52.666 --> 01:07:55.403
We need to make a splash if we're gonna
get renewed for a second season,

01:07:55.436 --> 01:07:56.838
am I right?
- Mm-hmm.

01:07:56.871 --> 01:07:58.873
Right. $250,000
is not gonna cut it

01:07:58.907 --> 01:08:00.609
if we want to attract
the best contestants.

01:08:00.641 --> 01:08:03.277
I thought they
weren't contestants.

01:08:03.311 --> 01:08:05.514
Are you finished?

01:08:05.547 --> 01:08:08.449
I'm thinking $1 million.
- A million?

01:08:08.483 --> 01:08:12.488
$1 million for the death of the
year on the season finale.

01:08:14.623 --> 01:08:15.590
We get the audience involved,

01:08:15.623 --> 01:08:17.559
we plaster billboards
all over the country,

01:08:17.591 --> 01:08:19.327
and the next thing you know
we're back on top,

01:08:19.359 --> 01:08:20.563
just like that.
Say yes.

01:08:23.899 --> 01:08:26.268
I'll talk to the network.
- No, no, no.

01:08:26.301 --> 01:08:27.703
I need a yes or a no.

01:08:29.904 --> 01:08:32.240
I'll convince them.
- Thank you.

01:09:33.902 --> 01:09:35.337
Hey.
- Hi.

01:09:35.368 --> 01:09:37.337
Uh, I forgot my run-down
for next week.

01:09:37.372 --> 01:09:40.709
You wouldn't happen to have
an extra one, would you?

01:09:40.742 --> 01:09:41.841
Oh.
- Yeah.

01:09:41.876 --> 01:09:44.444
Perfect. Thank you.

01:09:44.479 --> 01:09:46.182
Good night.
- Good night.

01:10:00.996 --> 01:10:03.632
Little man,
I've got a quest--

01:10:09.837 --> 01:10:10.872
Hey, where's Elliot?

01:10:10.905 --> 01:10:12.673
He was transferred to
palliative last night.

01:10:12.707 --> 01:10:15.244
What?

01:10:19.881 --> 01:10:20.849
Sorry.

01:10:20.881 --> 01:10:22.283
Excuse me.

01:10:24.685 --> 01:10:26.322
Oh, no.

01:10:28.756 --> 01:10:30.291
What are you doing here?

01:10:31.826 --> 01:10:36.265
No, no, oh, no.
No. You get out.

01:10:36.297 --> 01:10:37.765
Please, can I just say goodbye?
- No.

01:10:37.798 --> 01:10:41.802
No, you cannot. I told them
to keep you away from him.

01:10:41.836 --> 01:10:43.639
Don't you think you have
done enough to screw up

01:10:43.671 --> 01:10:47.041
the last few weeks
of my son's life?

01:10:47.074 --> 01:10:49.344
He is 11 years old,
for God's sake.

01:10:49.377 --> 01:10:51.313
You had him talking
about nothing but death.

01:10:51.345 --> 01:10:53.481
That wasn't me, I promise you. I
tried to stop him from watching--

01:10:53.515 --> 01:10:57.352
Fuck you! Fuck you,
you Satanist bitch!

01:10:57.385 --> 01:10:59.488
You brainwashed my son!

01:10:59.520 --> 01:11:00.988
<i>- Please...
- You stole his innocence.</i>

01:11:01.021 --> 01:11:03.958
I love your son. I just want
to say goodbye to him--

01:11:03.992 --> 01:11:06.528
Get out! You get out!
You get out!

01:11:06.560 --> 01:11:08.296
Get her out of here before I do!

01:11:08.329 --> 01:11:09.797
I'm sorry.

01:11:40.761 --> 01:11:41.764
Mr. Curtis?

01:11:43.265 --> 01:11:45.534
I spoke to a friend and he told me
you were a man who gets things done.

01:11:47.702 --> 01:11:50.639
I know you.
Mr. Washington, right?

01:11:50.671 --> 01:11:53.375
Yeah, you used to live
a few blocks away from here.

01:11:53.408 --> 01:11:56.712
Pretty wife, good job, a kid.

01:11:56.744 --> 01:11:59.414
Two now.
No job.

01:12:00.582 --> 01:12:01.883
You don't want
to be messing with me.

01:12:01.916 --> 01:12:03.518
No, no, no.
I don't want drugs.

01:12:03.551 --> 01:12:08.123
I hear that you loan money
to people in need sometimes.

01:12:08.155 --> 01:12:09.890
Not to people like you.

01:12:09.923 --> 01:12:11.726
Look, it's just a few thou.

01:12:11.760 --> 01:12:15.063
I'll pay you back, man.
I promise.

01:12:15.095 --> 01:12:16.931
And what happens if you don't?

01:12:18.800 --> 01:12:21.670
The streets ain't
for you no more.

01:12:21.703 --> 01:12:22.838
Drive.

01:12:47.828 --> 01:12:50.731
You're an abomination!

01:12:58.672 --> 01:13:02.676
Life is a gift!

01:13:02.710 --> 01:13:05.881
This is not the American way!

01:13:05.913 --> 01:13:08.849
Stop this madness!

01:13:13.454 --> 01:13:15.689
This is so wrong!

01:13:21.095 --> 01:13:23.899
<i>I'm here at the scene of
auditions for This Is Your Death.</i>

01:13:23.931 --> 01:13:25.900
There's a $1,000,000 prize.
But however,

01:13:25.934 --> 01:13:30.439
there are also allegations of faking
a death on a previous episode.

01:13:30.471 --> 01:13:31.939
We're hoping to find out
more today.

01:13:31.974 --> 01:13:34.676
As you know, we're running these
auditions throughout the country today,

01:13:34.708 --> 01:13:37.878
so there's no guarantee that
any of you will be selected.

01:13:37.912 --> 01:13:40.715
Our casting criteria
changes show by show,

01:13:40.747 --> 01:13:44.018
so all you need to do
is be yourselves

01:13:44.051 --> 01:13:47.154
and prove your willingness to go
through with your suicide on stage.

01:13:47.188 --> 01:13:49.658
Now, we're gonna set you up
with one of our psychiatrists

01:13:49.690 --> 01:13:52.126
who are gonna run you through
some questions. Cool?

01:13:55.930 --> 01:13:58.533
